        <meta name="og:description" content="There is near unanimous scientific consensus that greenhouse gas emissions generated
by human activity will change Earth's climate. The recent (globally averaged) warming
by 0·5°C is partly attributable to such anthropogenic emissions. Climate change will
affect human health in many ways—mostly adversely. Here, we summarise the epidemiological
evidence of how climate variations and trends affect various health outcomes. We assess
the little evidence there is that recent global warming has already affected some
health outcomes." />
    




